<br>
I personally follow the view of Peter Singer.  Some of these ideas are very unpopular.  Where do I draw the line?  I draw the line at suffering.  I think out of all feelings, that suffering is the worst that any animal can go through.  A two month old fetu does not suffer.  A person with a life ending disease does not suffer when they choose assisted suicide.  A carrot does not suffer.  What does suffer?  A cow at the slaughter house.  A abused human child.  A pet tied outside and ignored.<br>
<br>
That is where I draw the line.<br>
