So a cow that meets an equaly quick and arguably painless death suffers more? <br>
<br>
Trying to push being a Vegitarian because you think its &quot;healthy&quot; is one thing. Trying to push it because of the &quot;poor animals&quot; is another. <br>
<br>
Ive shot moose, did I feel pity for them? No I did not nor should I. Its not like the moose's poker buddys are gonna miss him next friday night. His wife isn't going to wonder when he is going to come home. And his kids being beasts driven by instinct alone don't even know they have a father in the true sense of the word.<br>
<br>
Did he feel pain? im sure he did, right up to the point I put a 30 ot six round through his eye. When you can prove to me that a unthinking beast has other unthinking beasts that will truly mourn his passing then ill rethink hunting meat. The same moose runs the risk of being slowly eaten alive by a bear every day of its life. Or breaking a leg and being draged down by a pack of wolfs and eaten to death. Or better yet starving to death during the long winter. I can think of many other things in nature that would have given it a much more horrible end than I did. A cow stuck in the same environment as the moose wouldn't last a week. So what do you prepose? We let loose all the cows and give them their god given right to freedom?<br>
<br>
People always make the comment &quot;we are animals to&quot;. Thats right we are animals to, and like other animals we feed ourselfs from other living things. Some with meat and vegetables others with just Vegatables. Its a matter of prefreance, and if you wan't to feel sorry for the animals. More power to you, its your right. But feeding us nonsensical philosiphy about the feelings of instinct drivin animal's isn't going to sway my opinion thats for sure. Call me ingrorant if you like, its not gonna hurt my feelings anymore than puting a slug through a moose hurt his <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 985<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 4:00:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1430.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ~(8^0)-I----&lt;</span><hr size=1> Many animals show mourning of their dead, from prairie dogs to elephants.<br>
